  "text": "A conclusive diagnostic criterion for BWI is not available, but we should consider an active enteritis affecting the ileum in a contiguous pattern from cecum with a similar or higher degree of inflammation. The differentiation of Crohn's ileocolitis and \"panulcerative\" colitis with BWI is direct when granulomas are found on \"histology or aphthous ulcers, cobblestoning, and skip lesions are seen endoscopically, but can be a clinical challenge when these features are absent\" [CITATION_1] .",
