      "span_text": "The differentiation of Crohn's ileocolitis and \"panulcerative\" colitis with BWI is direct when granulomas are found on \"histology or aphthous ulcers, cobblestoning, and skip lesions are seen endoscopically, but can be a clinical challenge when these features are absent\"  ."
